# SSH allowed-signers file (git gpg.ssh.allowedSignersFile format). Each line:
#   <email-or-principal> namespaces="git" <ssh-public-key>
#
# Only the people listed here may attest native/manual verification artifacts.
# This file is CODEOWNERS-protected (release/security reviewer). While it has no
# real entries, scripts/verify-attestations.sh SKIPS (template default). Add the
# testers' SSH signing public keys to activate enforcement, e.g.:
#
#   elleskay@example.com namespaces="git" ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5...
#
# Testers must also sign commits: `git config gpg.format ssh` and
# `git config user.signingkey <key>`, then commit with -S (or commit.gpgsign true).
